    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you begin, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken</strong> with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden, then transfer the chicken to a plate, set aside and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-miso-chicken-and-potato-casserole/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While your chicken is cooking, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your<strong> carrot[s] </strong>roughly</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[550ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-miso-chicken-and-potato-casserole/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Carefully wipe the reserved pan with some kitchen paper (it will be hot!) and return it to a medium-high heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </strong></span><strong>flour</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-miso-chicken-and-potato-casserole/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Strip your <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems (save some whole leaves for garnish!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-miso-chicken-and-potato-casserole/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>onion has softened, add the<strong> browned chicken</strong> with the <strong>chopped thyme</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Add your <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Then add your <strong>chicken stock</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> and <strong>chopped carrots</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for 30 min or until everything is tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-miso-chicken-and-potato-casserole/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are nearly done, slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until toasted</p><p>Spread a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> on the <strong>toasted ciabatta</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-miso-chicken-and-potato-casserole/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is tender, add your <strong>clotted cream </strong>and your<strong> miso </strong>to the pan with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and season with a very generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy miso chicken and potato casserole</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-miso-chicken-and-potato-casserole/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy miso chicken and potato casserole</strong> in bowls with the<strong> buttered ciabatta</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the remaining<strong> thyme leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
